The reflection coefficient for a 75-ohm load on a 50-ohm line is \(\Gamma = (75-50)/(75+50) = 0.2\), so the reflected power ratio is \(|\Gamma|^2 = 0.04\) or 4%.  
When a 50-ohm load is used, it matches the line impedance, so no power is reflected and all 50W is delivered to the load.  

